0we%20tend%20to%20eat%20more%20slowly%20when%20conversing%20and%20laughing%20with%20peers%2C%20Baum%20says.%20We%20usually%20pause%20more%20in%20between%20bites%2C%20which%20means%20we're%20likely%20to%20be%20more%20mindful%20of%20each%20bite%20and%20can%20better%20recognize%20our%20body's%20hunger%20and%20satiety%20cues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20noting%20that%20choosing%20dining%20mates%20may%20be%20as%20important%20as%20choosing%20dishes.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20those%20around%20us%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthy-eating-tips-food-routines-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeat%20healthy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nutrient-dense%20foods%2C%20Kumar%20says%20we're%20more%20likely%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2238c6cd73-de26-476a-8a65-5b046a6d37ca%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20change%20your%20eating%20habits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20have%20to%20go%20out%20when%20eating%20with%20others.%20Baum%20suggests%20initiating%20virtual%20meal%20dates%20with%20family%20or%20friends%2C%20potlucks%2C%20or%20neighborhood%20meals%20to%20mitigate%20our%20lonely%20eating%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaum%20added%20that%20the%20simple%20act%20of%20being%20more%20social%20can%20lead%20to%20more%20opportunities%20for%20communal%20eating.%20For%20example%2C%20joining%20clubs%20or%20activities%20often%20leads%20to%20people%20eating%20food%20together%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20do%20have%20to%20eat%20alone%2C%20Baum%20recommends%20engaging%20in%20non-technological%20activities%20at%20the%20table%2C%20like%20reading%20a%20book%20or%20magazine.%20Flipping%20pages%20can%20slow%20the%20eating%20process%2C%20giving%20you%20time%20to%20savor%20your%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20improve%20the%20experience%20of%20eating%20alone%20by%20establishing%20a%20mealtime%20routine%2C%20such%20as%20sitting%20in%20a%20regular%20spot%20and%20being%20mindful%20of%20your%20intake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a8a2