india.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fsimi-garewal-delets-the-post-she-shared-to-defend-abhishek-bachchan-amid-divorce-rumors-with-aishwarya-rai%2Farticleshow%2F115017943.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2278-Year-Old%20Donald%20Trump%20Oldest%20Person%20To%20Be%20Elected%20US%20President%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%20went%20from%20being%20a%20businessman%2C%20real%20estate%20tycoon%20and%20reality%20TV%20star%20to%20becoming%20the%20country's%20first%20former%20US%20President%20to%20be%20declared%20a%20convicted%20felon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20after%20surviving%20two%20assassination%20bids%20during%20his%202024%20campaign%2C%20the%2078-year-old%20remains%20unstoppable%20with%20American%20voters%20giving%20him%20a%20second%20term.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20he%20shattered%20the%20dream%20of%20the%20Democratic%20Party%2C%20as%20well%20as%20that%20of%20millions%20of%20Kamala%20Harris%20supporters%2C%20to%20finally%20have%20the%20first%20woman%20President%20in%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20now%20the%20oldest%20person%20in%20US%20history%20to%20be%20elected%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20time%20he%20left%20office%20after%20his%20loss%20in%20the%202020%20presidential%20election%20to%20his%20nomination%20as%20the%20Republican%20candidate%20in%20the%202024%20race%2C%20Trump%20continued%20to%20dominate%20the%20American%20news%20cycle%20and%20the%20country's%20psyche.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20November%202020%20result%20that%20brought%20Joe%20Biden%20to%20the%20White%20House%2C%20and%20a%20stunned%20nation%20watched%20his%20supporters%20storm%20the%20US%20Capitol%20on%20January%206.%20The%20riots%20disrupted%20a%20joint%20session%20of%20the%20US%20Congress%20which%20was%20in%20the%20process%20of%20affirming%20the%20presidential%20election%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20third%20run%20for%20the%20job%20in%202024%20was%20characterised%20by%20a%20slew%20of%20indictments%20and%20criminal%20cases%2C%20and%20a%20conviction%20in%20a%20New%20York%20court%20--%20making%20him%20the%20first%20former%20US%20president%20to%20be%20held%20guilty%20of%20a%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20grand%20jury%20found%20him%20guilty%20on%2034%20counts%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records.%20The%20Biden-Harris%20campaign%20said%20at%20the%20time%20that%20no%20one%20is%20above%20the%20law%20while%20Trump%20called%20the%20verdict%20the%20result%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Brigged%26quot%3B%20political%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20none%20of%20this%20could%20deter%20his%20ardent%20supporters%2C%20who%20rallied%20behind%20him%20and%20his%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vehement%20support%20was%20on%20full%20display%20in%20Milwaukee%20in%20July%20when%20Trump%2C%20with%20a%20bandaged%20ear%20after%20having%20survived%20an%20assassination%20attempt%2C%20arrived%20for%20the%20Republican%20National%20Convention%20to%20formally%20accept%20the%20party's%20nomination%20for%20President%20for%20the%20third%20consecutive%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20bullet%20in%20the%20upper%20part%20of%20his%20right%20ear%20when%20a%20shooter%20fired%20multiple%20shots%20at%20his%20election%20rally%20in%20Pennsylvania.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20born%20in%20Queens%2C%20New%20York%2C%20on%20June%2014%2C%201946%2C%20to%20Mary%20and%20Fred%20Trump%2C%20a%20successful%20real%20estate%20developer%2C%20as%20the%20fourth%20of%20their%20five%20children.%20He%20earned%20a%20degree%20in%20finance%20from%20the%20Wharton%20School%20of%20Finance%20and%20Commerce%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20in%201968.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20taking%20over%20his%20father's%20company%20in%201971%2C%20he%20renamed%20it%20the%20Trump%20Organisation%20and%20soon%20diversified%20into%20projects%20like%20hotels%2C%20resorts%2C%20residential%20and%20commercial%20buildings%2C%20casinos%20and%20golf%20courses.%20Trump%20also%20dabbled%20in%20Reality%20TV%20with%20'The%20Apprentice'%20in%202004%20that%20made%20him%20a%20household%20name%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20married%20Ivana%20Zelnickova%2C%20a%20Czech%20athlete%20and%20model%2C%20but%20divorced%20her%20in%201990.%20The%20couple%20has%20three%20children%20--%20Donald%20Jr%2C%20Ivanka%20and%20Eric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20married%20actor%20Marla%20Maples%20in%201993%20but%20divorced%20in%201999.%20They%20have%20an%20only%20child%2C%20Tiffany.%20Trump's%20current%20wife%20Melania%2C%20whom%20he%20married%20in%202005%2C%20is%20a%20former%20Slovenian%20model.%20They%20have%20a%20son%2C%20Barron%20William%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202016%20presidential%20race%2C%20fighting%20as%20a%20Republican%20nominee%20in%20the%20presidential%20race%2C%20Trump%20won%20against%20the%20Democratic%20nominee%20Hillary%20Clinton.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20election%20took%20place%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20concerns%20over%20the%20economy%2C%20illegal%20immigration%20and%20the%20wars%20in%20west%20Asia%20and%20Europe.%20Trump's%20support%20base%20saw%20him%20as%20the%20only%20one%20who%20could%20offer%20solutions%20to%20these.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20end%20the%20illegal%20immigration%20crisis%20by%20closing%20our%20border%20and%20finishing%20the%20wall%2C%20most%20of%20which%20I've%20already%20built%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20told%20cheering%20supporters%20at%20his%20party's%20national%20convention%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20country's%20southern%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20vowed%20that%20if%20he%20returned%20to%20the%20White%20House%2C%20%26quot%3Binflation%20will%20vanish%20completely%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20pledged%20to%20end%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20after%20Ukraine%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20reached%20out%20to%20congratulate%20him%20on%20his%20Republican%20presidential%20nomination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%2C%20as%20your