0rates%20were%20near%20zero%2C%20and%20real%20returns%20in%20bonds%20were%20lacking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20investors%20added%20them%20to%20their%20portfolios%20because%20history%20has%20shown%20us%20that%20asset%20classes%20can%20zig%20and%20zag%2C%20with%20long%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-and-bond-market-correlation-normal-2014-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperiods%20of%20stock%20market%20outperformance%3C%2Fa%3E%20relative%20to%20bonds%20and%20intervals%20where%20that%20dynamic%20flipped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20two%20years%20were%20great%20for%20both%20asset%20classes.%20Elevated%20rates%20put%20the%20bond%20market%20back%20on%20investors'%20minds%2C%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20a%20solid%2026%25%20total%20return.%20But%20depending%20on%20who%20you%20ask%2C%20the%20future%20may%20not%20be%20as%20bright.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYields%20will%20be%20less%20attractive%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-federal-reserve-election-jerome-powell-inflation-jobs-2024-11%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Fed%2520cut%2520interest%2520rates%2Ccountry%2520recovered%2520from%2520the%2520pandemic.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFed%20begins%20its%20rate%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20this%20cycle.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20expects%20stock-market%20returns%20to%20be%20muted%20for%20the%20coming%20decade.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20predicted%20to%20see%20a%20mere%203%25%20annualized%20return%20over%20the%20next%2010%20years%2C%20which%20could%20lag%20the%2010-year%20Treasury%20at%20an%20expected%204%25%20yield%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-beat-stock-market-returns-next-decade-goldman-sachs-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20investment%20bank's%20chief%20US%20equity%20strategist%20David%20Kostin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20bears%20are%20right%2C%20investors%20may%20be%20forced%20to%20take%20on%20more%20risk%20for%20returns.%20Sounds%20gloomy%2C%20but%20for%20bond%20traders%20like%20Mark%20Rieder%2C%20who%20has%20over%20two%20decades%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20sector%2C%20it%20could%20be%20an%20opportunity%20to%20dig%20for%20bargains%20in%20corporate%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerating%20alpha%20for%20a%20credit%20trader%20could%20mean%20beating%20a%20peer%2C%20a%20Bloomberg%20fixed%20income%20index%20that%20matches%20the%20category%20of%20bonds%20traded%2C%20or%20simply%20remaining%20in%20positive%20territory%20in%20terms%20of%20total%20returns%20when%20the%20market%20is%20down%2C%20Rieder%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%2010%20years%2C%20when%20interest%20rates%20were%20very%20low%2C%20it%20was%20not%20an%20exciting%20time%20to%20be%20a%20credit%20analyst%20and%20a%20portfolio%20manager%2C%26quot%3B%20Rieder%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20much%20more%20interesting%20today%2C%20and%20I'm%20really%20excited%20about%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20active%20debt%20investing%20takes%20a%20good%20level%20of%20skill%20and%20consistent%20effort%20to%20make%20the%20right%20credit%20selection%2C%20according%20to%20his%20new%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BReminiscences%20of%20a%20Bond%20Operator.%26quot%3B%20Like%20the%20stock-picking%20process%2C%20following%20the%20crowd%20or%20consensus%20won't%20result%20in%20alpha.%20A%20credit%20trader%20must%20conduct%20the%20same%20level%20of%20fundamental%20analysis%20and%20dig%20into%20a%20company's%20balance%20sheet%2C%20earnings%20calls%2C%2010Qs%2C%20and%2010Ks%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20to%20determine%20valuation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20always%20believed%20that%20a%20good%20credit%20analyst%20is%20also%20a%20really%20good%20equity%20analyst%20because%20you%20really%20need%20to%20understand%20the%20capital%20structure%20of%20the%20companies%20that%20you're%20evaluating%20and%20all%20of%20their%20different%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20Rieder%20said.%20%26quot%3BMost%20companies%20want%20to%20have%20their%20stock%20price%20go%20up%2C%20and%20so%20as%20a%20credit%20analyst%2C%20you%20need%20to%20understand%20that%20so%20that%20you%20can%20understand%20what%20their%20motivations%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20especially%20important%20now%2C%20as%20the%20credit%20space%20faces%20its%20own%20set%20of%20challenges.%20Like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fare-we-in-a-recession%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebusiness%20cycle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20credit%20has%20its%20booms%20and%20busts%20based%20on%20macro%20conditions%20and%20supply%20and%20demand.%20In%20a%20strong%20economic%20environment%2C%20corporate%20cash%20flows%20rise%2C%20and%20companies%20increase%20borrowing%20with%20favorable%20lending%20terms.%20But%20when%20times%20are%20tight%2C%20companies%20deleverage%20until%20their%20debt%20is%20less%20than%20their%20cash%20flow.%20Once%20that%20equilibrium%20is%20satisfied%2C%20more%20borrowing%20ensues%2C%20according%20to%20his%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERieder%20said%20credit%20is%20in%20the%20boom%20part%20of%20the%20cycle.%20This%20might%20sound%20surprising%2C%20considering%20debt%20has%20been%20expensive%20for%20the%20better%20part%20of%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20But%20most%20companies%20were%20locked%20into%20low%20yields%20before%20rates%20rose%2C%20he%20noted.%20As%20debt%20turnover%20increases%2C%20investors%20need%20to%20be%20cautious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lag%20impact%20on%20the%20increase%20in%20rates.%20Most%20companies%20borrow%20for%20long%20periods%20of%20time%2C%20five%20years%2C%2010%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Rieder%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20companies%20issued%20debt%20when%20interest%20rates%20were%20very%20low.%20They're%20now%20only%20starting%20to%20refinance%20that%20low-coupon%20debt.%20That%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20is%20what%20causes%20an%20impact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20doesn't%20expect%20that%20the%20Fed's%20cutting%20cycle%20will%20mitigate%20the%20crunch.%20The%20central%20bank%20can%20impact%20front-end%20yields%2C%20but%20the%20back%20end%20is%20driven%20by%20additional%20considerations%2C%20he%20noted.%20The%2010-year%20rose%20to%204.3%25%20shortly%20after%20the%20first%20rate%20cut%20of%20September%2C%20a%20signal%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-election-forecast-most-accurate-economist-predicts-outcome-economic-impact-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestors%20were%20looking%20ahead%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20other%20economic%20risk%20factors%2C%20including%20concerns%20over%20the%20government's%20ballooning%20deficit%2C%20he%20added.%20Additionally%2C%20economic%20conditions%20such%20as%20elevated%20credit%20card%20debt%20pose%20concerns%20for%20future%20corporate%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22101d0bc7-10c7-46f9-a758-eea160588283%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrading%20credit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20investment-grade%20credit%20spreads%20are%20tight.%20The%20yields%20in%20corporate%20bonds%20aren't%20much%20higher%20than%20in%20government%20bonds%2C%20meaning%20less%20compensation%20for%20more%20risk.%20But%20if%20we%20move%20from%20the%20boom%20to%20the%20bust%20phase%2C%20credit%20spreads%20could%20widen%2C%20and%20that%20could%20create%20opportunities%20in%20the%20credit%20space%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20spreads%20are%20tight%2C%20he%20prefers%20front-end%20yield%20or%20pairing%20trades%20with%20cheap%20optionality.%20The%20cost%20of%20shorting%20a%20credit%20index%20like%20the%20CDX%20Investment%20Grade%205-Year%20Index%2C%20a%20credit-default-swap%20index%20that%20tracks%20the%20credit%20risk%20of%20large%20US%20investment-grade%20companies%2C%20is%20low.%20And%20since%20spreads%20are%20trading%20at%20historically%20tight%20levels%2C%20it's%20less%20likely%20to%20get%20much%20lower%2C%20which%20could%20limit%20potential%20losses%2C%20he%20said.%20This%20position%20can%20then%20be%20paired%20with%20a%20trade%20expected%20to%20perform%20positively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20example%20he%20provides%20of%20a%20market-neutral%20pair%20trade%20could%20look%20like%20buying%20a%20corporate%20bond%20in%20a%20sector%20with%20structural%20tailwinds%2C%20such%20as%20a%20natural%20gas%20producer%20set%20to%20benefit%20from%20increased%20demand%20and%20rising%20energy%20prices%2C%20or%20airplane%20lessors%20who%20benefit%20from%20higher%20lease%20rates%20due%20to%20a%20tight%20aircraft%20supply%20%E2%80%94%20a%20situation%20that's%20unlikely%20to%20ease%20in%20the%20near%20term%20because%20of%20production%20challenges%20faced%20by%20manufacturers.%20Then%2C%20take%20a%20short%20position%20in%20an%20interest-rate%20future%20to%20hedge%20against%20the%20bond's%20interest-rate%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20trade%20works%20if%20natural%20gas%20prices%20remain%20stable%20or%20rise%2C%20leading%20the%20energy%20bond%20to%20outperform%20the%20overall%20corporate%20bond%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Rieder%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20excellent%20opportunity%20to%20capitalize%20on%20the%20current%20tight%20credit%20spread%20conditions%20and%20complacency%20in%20the%20overall%20credit%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20liquidity%20can%20also%20give%20you%20an%20upper%20hand.%20As%20spreads%20widen%2C%20investors%20may%20be%20forced%20into%20selling%20higher-quality%20credit%20because%20they%20can't%20offload%20the%20lower-quality%20ones%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20huge%20opportunities%20in%20credit%20if%20you%20remain%20liquid%20during%20dislocations%2C%26quot%3B%20Rieder%20said.%20%26quot%3BOther%20investors%20are%20going%20to%20be%20looking%20for%20liquidity.%20They%20can't%20sell%20what%20they%20want%20to%2C%