or%20free.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Skylar%20Griffin%2C%20a%2021-year-old%20college%20student%20in%20Georgia.%20Griffin%20financial%20claims%20have%20been%20verified%20with%20documentation.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20a%20child%2C%20my%20mom%20often%20shared%20financial%20advice.%20She%20told%20us%20never%20to%20cosign%20for%20someone's%20loan%20and%20don't%20buy%20anything%20unless%20we%20could%20buy%20it%20twice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20several%20occasions%2C%20she%20advised%20us%20kids%20never%20to%20get%20a%20credit%20card%20unless%20we%20were%20responsible%20enough%20to%20pay%20it%20off%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20didn't%20want%20us%20to%20struggle%20financially%20like%20she%20did%20as%20a%20single%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20high%20school%2C%20I%20started%20watching%20YouTube%20videos%20about%20finances.%20I%20saw%20financial%20struggles%20firsthand%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20in%20that%20position%20as%20an%20adult.%20The%20videos%20taught%20me%20I'd%20need%20to%20build%20up%20my%20credit%20score%20to%20buy%20a%20car%20or%20a%20house%20or%20if%20I%20might%20need%20a%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22102ef261-a63c-412a-8936-6e2d5bc894d4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20got%20my%20first%20credit%20card%20before%20going%20to%20college%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202021%2C%20I%20was%20preparing%20to%20study%20business%20management%20at%20Columbus%20State%20University%20in%20the%20fall.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20my%20mom's%20knowledge%2C%20I%20ordered%20a%20Bank%20of%20America%20student%20card.%20It%20was%20a%20Visa%20card%20with%20no%20annual%20fees.%20My%20mom%20wasn't%20happy.%20I%20reassured%20her%20I'd%20done%20my%20research%20and%20could%20handle%20the%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20college%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20a%20call%20center%20during%20the%20school%20year%2C%20paid%20internships%20in%20the%20summer%2C%20and%20received%20refund%20checks%20because%20my%20scholarship%20was%20more%20than%20school%20costs.%20I%20also%20earned%20a%20bit%20of%20money%20doing%20social%20media%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20card%20had%20a%20limit%20of%20%24500.%20I%20would%20buy%20little%20things%20here%20and%20there%2C%20making%20sure%20I%20had%20enough%20in%20my%20checking%20or%20savings%20account%20to%20pay%20it%20off%20each%20month.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20marked%20all%20the%20due%20dates%20in%20my%20calendar%2C%20and%20I%20was%20never%20late%20for%20a%20credit%20card%20payment.%20There%20were%20temptations%20to%20buy%20new%20clothes%20or%20tech%2C%20but%20I%20always%20fought%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc7cfef9-313f-436d-be60-a1a46519f707%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20an%20AmEx%20for%20the%20travel%20points%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20kept%20using%20the%20Bank%20of%20America%20card%20throughout%20my%20freshman%20and%20sophomore%20years%20of%20college%2C%20but%20in%20April%202023%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20out%20an%20Amex%20Gold%20card%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20heard%20about%20travel%20credit%20cards%20through%20watching%20financial%20advice%20videos%20online.%20If%20I%20used%20this%20card%20for%20buying%20groceries%20or%20dining%20out%2C%20my%20two%20main%20expenses%20in%20college%2C%20I%20would%20get%20four%20times%20the%20points%20to%20use%20on%20travel.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20wasn't%20traveling%20much%2C%20I%20planned%20to%20travel.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20card%20had%20a%20%24250%20annual%20fee%2C%20which%20was%20worth%20it%20for%20the%20points%20I%20felt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20only%20used%20my%20card%20for%20things%20I%20needed%20or%20had%20saved%20for.%20I%20never%20bought%20things%20just%20to%20earn%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202024%2C%20I%20took%20a%20big%20leap%20and%20opened%20an%20Amex%20Platinum%20credit%20card.%20It%20comes%20with%20a%20high%20price%20tag%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%24695%20annual%20fee%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20thought%20the%20benefits%20outweighed%20the%20price.%20Because%20it%20was%20another%20Amex%20card%2C%20all%20of%20my%20points%20were%20added%20to%20the%20points%20earned%20from%20the%20Amex%20Gold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20only%20use%20this%20card%20for%20booking%20flights%20and%20hotels%20because%20this%20is%20what%20I%20get%20the%20highest%20points%20for.%20With%20the%20card%2C%20I%20get%20five%20times%20the%20points%20when%20booking%20flights%20and%20hotels%2C%20a%20%24200%20yearly%20airline%20credit%2C%20and%20a%20%24200%20yearly%20hotel%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20stay%20at%20Marriott%20or%20Hilton%2C%20I%20get%20'high%20status'%20and%20often%20get%20my%20room%20upgraded.%20But%20my%20favourite%20perk%20is%20the%20CLEAR%20Plus%20membership%20which%20gets%20me%20through%20TSA%20quicker%20at%20the%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I%20was%20planning%20some%20big%20trips%20in%202024%20to%20Japan%20and%20New%20York%2C%20and%20then%20a%20cruise%20to%20the%20Bahamas%2C%20so%20planned%20to%20make%20all%20my%20travel%20purchases%20on%20the%20Platinum.%20Since%20getting%20an%20Amex%2C%20I've%20been%20able%20to%20fly%20to%20Japan%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20Miami%20for%20free%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20card%2C%20I%20accessed%20airport%20lounges%20on%20the%20long%20trip%20to%20Japan%20and%20was%20part%20of%20the%20President's%20Circle%20with%20Hertz%20Car%20Rentals%2C%20so%20I%20was%20guaranteed%20a%20car%20upgrade%20when%20I%20rented%20a%20car%20to%20get%20around%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec2f29ef-d145-470e-972f-0e160d4e0cd5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20took%20out%20a%20fourth%20credit%20card%20so%20I%20could%20earn%20points%20for%20other%20purchases%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202024%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20out%20another%20Amex%20card%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Amex%20Blue%20Business%20Plus.%20This%20card%20means%20I%20can%20earn%20points%20paying%20for%20things%20like%20gas%2C%20that%20don't%20earn%20me%20points%20on%20my%20other%20cards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20annual%20fee%2C%20and%20I%20could%20only%20take%20it%20out%20because%20I'm%20considered%20a%20sole%20proprietor.%20I%20own%20a%20Mercari%20shop%20where%20I%20resell%20vintage%20clothes%20I%20find%20at%20flea%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20only%20use%20my%20Bank%20of%20America%20card%20when%20Amex%20isn't%20accepted.%20I%20never%20use%20a%20debit%20card%20unless%20I'm%20pulling%20cash%20out%20of%20the%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20I%20am%20confident%20and%20comfortable%20using%20credit%20cards%2C%20I%20still%20don't%20spend%20anything%20that%20isn't%20in%20my%20checking%20or%20savings%20account.%20I%20never%20base%20a%20purchase%20on%20the%20money%20that%20I'm%20expecting%20in%20my%20account%2C%20because%20you%20never%20know%20how%20finances%20could%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20put%20all%20my%20due%20dates%20in%20my%20calendar%20and%20aim%20to%20pay%20each%20of%20them%20off%20earlier%20than%20required.%20Sometimes%2C%20I%20feel%20the%20urge%20to%20overspend.%20But%20then%20I%20remember%20the%20interest%20rates%20on%20my%20cards%2C%20and%20I%20snap%20back%20to%20reality.%20Paying%20high%20interest%20because%20I%20can't%20afford%20to%20pay%20my%20bill%20in%20full%20is%20not%20worth%20the%20momentary%20satisfaction%20of%20shopping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20all%20the%20benefits%20I've%20received%20when%20traveling%2C%20my%20credit%20cards%20helped%20me%20raise%20my%20credit%20score%20to%20755.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221abacec9-c073-4582-ac5e-15c3908118fc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20never%20stop%20learning%20about%20finance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20college%20students%20should%20consider%20getting%20a%20student%20credit%20card%20with%20no%20fee.%20They%20have%20low%20limits%20and%20can%20help%20start%20building%20a%20credit%20score.%20However%2C%20if%20you're%20impulsive%20or%20have%20poor%20spending%20habits%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20recommend%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20now%20says%20she's%20proud%20of%20how%20I%20manage%20my%20finances.%20I've%20always%20found%20personal%20finance%20interesting%20and%20the%20concepts%20easy%20to%20understand%2C%20but%20it%20takes%20dedication%20to%20stay%20on%20track%20financially.%20I%20never%20stop%20learning%20to%20make%20sure%20I'm%20doing%20what's%20best%20for%20my%20financial%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famex-credit-cards-platinum-points-travel-gen-z-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730889565000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672b3ddc88cea3ba1c1e9d3e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famex-credit-cards-platinum-points-travel-gen-z-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Gen%20Z%20student%20with%20a%20Gold%2C%20Platinum%20and%20Blue%20Business%20AmEx%20shares%20how%20she%20maximises%20points%20to%20travel%20more%20affordably%20and%20improve%20her%20credit%20score.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Lauren%20Crosby%20Medlicott)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famex-credit-cards-platinum-points-travel-gen-z-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Putin%20May%20Not%20Congratulate%20Trump%20Over%20US%20Election%20Results%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20said%20Wednesday%20it%20would%20judge%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20who%20claimed%20victory%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmagnificent-victory-for-american-people-donald-trump-on-us-election-result-6955510%5C%22%3EUS%20presidential%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%20his%20actions%20and%20that%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20had%20no%20plans%20to%20congratulate%20him.%3C